Black Marsh

Summary:

  • Homeland of the Argonians.

  • Makes up the southeastern part of Tamriel.

  • It is the Amazon Rainforest of Tamriel, very dangerous to inexperienced foreigners.

  • Borders Morrowind to the north, and Cyrodiil to the west.

Argonians

Illustration of an Argonian male

Real-world counterpart/inspiration:

Mesoamerica (Aztec, Mayan)

Geographic features:

  • Consists of very dense swampland region and lush humid jungles that are teeming with posionous plants and violent predators.

  • The land of Black Marsh is very hostile to outsiders that are not adapted to the almost-sentient swamps, especially further inland.

  • The region's tropical climate lends its plants the capacity to overturn all attempts to cultivate them.

  • There are few roads, and the principal method of travel is by boat.

  • Foreign ventures beyond the slave-trade have met with abject failure; only the native peoples and the sapient Hist trees can thrive here.

  • Most of the Argonian population reside in the inland waterways and swamps of the southern interior.

  • The regions of Black Marsh are varied and difficult to map; categorizing which region a city belongs to is unclear, but here is what is currently known:
  • Arnesia
    • A region somewhere in the eastern parts of Black Marsh, roughly in between the cities of Thorn and Archon.
    • There is a round island off the east coast of the area, known to consist of dark green/gray terrain.
  • Gloomire
    • Western swampy region in Black Marsh.
    • Contains the city of Gideon.
    • Being next to the Cyrodiil border, this frontier region is the gateway before the more treacherous parts of Black Marsh.

      • Gloomire

  • Middle Argonia
    • This region is the impenetrable center, the dark heart of Black Marsh.
    • The marsh becomes extremely dense here, and the mud is said to take on a pitch-black hue.
    • Only Argonians can survive here.
    • Has the most amount of Hist trees and, therefore, Argonian tribes.
    • Contains the city of Helstrom.
    • All river systems in Black Marsh flow into Middle Argonia.
  • Murkmire
    • Coastal region in southern Black Marsh.
    • Contains the port city of Lilmoth.
    • Murkmire is inhabited by both Argonian and Naga tribes.

      • Murkmire

  • Shadowfen
    • Northwest region of Black Marsh.
    • Borders Morrowind to the north and Cyrodiil to the west.
    • Contains the city of Stormhold.
    • Being next to Morrowind, it is the most prone to raids by Dunmer slavers.

      • Shadowfen

  • Thornmarsh
    • Coastal region in northeastern Black Marsh.
    • Contains the city of Thorn.
    • Has more temperate grasslands compared to the swampier areas further south.
